go/middleware/fake.go.message:
Opening /dev/zero and reading from it is really inefficient.  I would just make a ZeroReader that's something like,

func (ctx *ZeroReader) Read(p []byte) (int, error) {
  for i := range p {
    p[i] = 0
  }
  return len(p), nil
}

Then wrap that in an io.LimitReader down below.

